                <h2>Why Weekly Compliance Audits Are Essential</h2>
<p>Overseas advertising involves multi-platform and multi-regional policy differences. Major platforms like Meta, Google, and TikTok update their advertising policies monthly with increasing frequency. A small oversight can lead to ad disapprovals, account restrictions, or permanent bans within 48 hours. A utility app team once had 3 ad campaigns disabled in a single day due to a missing privacy policy link on their landing page, costing approximately $2,000 in wasted spend before identifying the issue.</p>
<p>This SOP applies to operations teams managing 2 or more advertising accounts. It is recommended to execute on Friday afternoons, with a total time commitment of 30 minutes.</p>
<h2>Pre-Audit Preparation</h2>
<p>Before beginning the inspection, complete the following preparations in order:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Log into ad platforms</strong> — Confirm you are using admin-level access to avoid permission issues</li>
<li><strong>Open audit records</strong> — Use online spreadsheets (Google Sheets or Feishu) for team collaboration</li>
<li><strong>Prepare checklist</strong> — Print this SOP for desk reference until you memorize the process</li>
<li><strong>Check recent policy updates</strong> — Log into each platform's policy center to review announcements from the past 2 weeks</li>
</ol>
<h2>7-Step Compliance Audit Process</h2>
<h3>Step 1: Account Status Check</h3>
<p>Access the ad management dashboard and check the following status for each account:</p>
<ul>
<li>Is the account "Active" with no restriction alerts</li>
<li>Is billing information complete and payment method valid</li>
<li>Are security settings enabled (2FA, user permission levels)</li>
</ul>
<p>If abnormalities are found, immediately screenshot and contact platform support while pausing related campaigns.</p>
<h3>Step 2: Ad Creative Compliance Review</h3>
<p>Focus on these high-risk issues:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Prohibited terms</strong>: absolute claims like "best," "#1," "only," "top"</li>
<li><strong>Exaggerated claims</strong>: "100% effective," "guaranteed cure," "assured returns"</li>
<li><strong>Copyright issues</strong>: Unauthorized brand logos, celebrity images, film screenshots</li>
<li><strong>Targeting implications</strong>: Ads must not imply targeting specific groups (such as particular races, age discrimination)</li>
</ul>
<p>Flag suspected non-compliant creatives as "pending review" and complete modifications or removal within 24 hours.</p>
<h3>Step 3: Landing Page Compliance Verification</h3>
<p>Landing pages clicked from ads must meet these requirements:</p>
<ul>
<li>Pages load normally without 404 or server errors</li>
<li>Privacy policy page exists with valid links</li>
<li>Cookie notices or pop-ups comply with GDPR/CCPA requirements</li>
<li>Refund policies are clearly visible (required for e-commerce ads)</li>
<li>Contact information (email or phone) is real and verifiable</li>
</ul>
<p>Use incognito browser mode to spot-check each campaign, focusing on landing pages created in the last 7 days.</p>
<h3>Step 4: Delivery Qualification Verification</h3>
<p>Different product categories require corresponding delivery qualifications:</p>
<ul>
<li>Financial products: Confirm possession of relevant financial regulatory certificates</li>
<li>Pharmaceutical products: Comply with destination country drug advertising regulations</li>
<li>Alcohol products: Confirm the投放地区 allows alcohol advertising with correct age targeting</li>
<li>Children-related products: Comply with COPPA and other children's privacy protection laws</li>
</ul>
<p>If qualifications are expired or missing, immediately pause related ads and supplement materials.</p>
<h3>Step 5: Budget and Spend Reconciliation</h3>
<ul>
<li>Verify daily budgets match plans with no abnormal fluctuations</li>
<li>Confirm spend curves are normal, excluding bot traffic</li>
<li>Verify conversion attribution windows are reasonable to avoid data distortion from overly long windows</li>
<li>Confirm budget allocation is even to avoid triggering risk controls through excessive single-day spending</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 6: Audience Targeting Audit</h3>
<p>Review audience settings for discriminatory targeting or sensitive segments:</p>
<ul>
<li>Exclude culturally sensitive segments like "multicultural affinity"</li>
<li>Confirm age targeting aligns with product's intended users</li>
<li>Exclude vulnerable groups you do not want to reach</li>
<li>Geographic targeting matches regions supported by the landing page</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 7: Data and Privacy Compliance</h3>
<ul>
<li>Confirm ad pixel installation is correct with normal data transmission</li>
<li>Check SDK integration does not collect excessive user data</li>
<li>Verify UTM parameter settings are standardized for tracking投放效果</li>
<li>Confirm data transmission with analytics tools complies with privacy agreements</li>
</ul>
<h2>Common Violation Quick Reference</h2>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Violation Type</th>
<th>Typical Example</th>
<th>Remediation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Absolute claims</td>
<td>"The best VPN service"</td>
<td>Change to "Leading VPN service"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Efficacy promises</td>
<td>"Lose 10 jin in 7 days, guaranteed"</td>
<td>Change to "Helps manage body shape"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Vague pricing</td>
<td>"Only 99"</td>
<td>Change to "Limited time $99 (valid until X/X)"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Missing privacy</td>
<td>No privacy policy on landing page</td>
<td>Add privacy policy page and link from ads</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Missing qualifications</td>
<td>Promoting financial products without license</td>
<td>Add qualifications or remove ads</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h2>Audit Records and Review</h2>
<p>After completing all checks, fill in the following in your audit record sheet:</p>
<ul>
<li>Audit date and person executing</li>
<li>Check results for each account (Pass / Pending / Abnormal)</li>
<li>Issues found and priority (P0 immediate / P1 within 24 hours / P2 this week)</li>
<li>Issue resolution status and next review date</li>
</ul>
<p>It is recommended to hold a monthly review meeting to analyze high-frequency violations, optimize the checklist, and update technical documentation.</p>
<h2>Closing</h2>
<p>Compliance auditing is not reactive work of "fixing problems after they occur" but should be a proactive mechanism for risk prevention. Consistently dedicating 30 minutes weekly to systematic checks can reduce account ban rates by over 80% while reducing budget waste from violations. Team leaders should include compliance audits in performance metrics to ensure this SOP is genuinely implemented.</p>
